      "revid": 188228,
      "text": {
        "*": "<div class=\"mw-parser-output\"><p>Let <img src=\"//latex.artofproblemsolving.com/6/6/9/66981fa3920210c6ad8dbe5e968783d5dd7520c3.png\" class=\"latex\" alt=\"$\\gamma$\" style=\"vertical-align: -3px\" width=\"10\" height=\"11\" /> be circle and let <img src=\"//latex.artofproblemsolving.com/4/b/4/4b4cade9ca8a2c8311fafcf040bc5b15ca507f52.png\" class=\"latex\" alt=\"$P$\" width=\"14\" height=\"12\" /> be a point outside <img src=\"//latex.artofproblemsolving.com/6/6/9/66981fa3920210c6ad8dbe5e968783d5dd7520c3.png\" class=\"latex\" alt=\"$\\gamma$\" style=\"vertical-align: -3px\" width=\"10\" height=\"11\" />. Let <img src=\"//latex.artofproblemsolving.com/3/7/7/377291318df52e4f013ab2bf28ee82454a9e57da.png\" class=\"latex\" alt=\"$PA$\" width=\"27\" height=\"13\" /> and <img src=\"//latex.artofproblemsolving.com/9/f/9/9f988caff51f7fc88ad40d1d25022c52ffd8f976.png\" class=\"latex\" alt=\"$PB$\" width=\"28\" height=\"12\" /> be the tangents from <img src=\"//latex.artofproblemsolving.com/4/b/4/4b4cade9ca8a2c8311fafcf040bc5b15ca507f52.png\" class=\"latex\" alt=\"$P$\" width=\"14\" height=\"12\" /> to <img src=\"//latex.artofproblemsolving.com/6/6/9/66981fa3920210c6ad8dbe5e968783d5dd7520c3.png\" class=\"latex\" alt=\"$\\gamma$\" style=\"vertical-align: -3px\" width=\"10\" height=\"11\" /> (where <img src=\"//latex.artofproblemsolving.com/0/a/7/0a7d222b94139d1bb2d5ca30d2331fa3dd401e37.png\" class=\"latex\" alt=\"$A, B \\in \\gamma$\" style=\"vertical-align: -3px\" width=\"68\" height=\"16\" />). A line passing through <img src=\"//latex.artofproblemsolving.com/4/b/4/4b4cade9ca8a2c8311fafcf040bc5b15ca507f52.png\" class=\"latex\" alt=\"$P$\" width=\"14\" height=\"12\" /> intersects <img src=\"//latex.artofproblemsolving.com/6/6/9/66981fa3920210c6ad8dbe5e968783d5dd7520c3.png\" class=\"latex\" alt=\"$\\gamma$\" style=\"vertical-align: -3px\" width=\"10\" height=\"11\" /> at points <img src=\"//latex.artofproblemsolving.com/9/8/6/9866e3a998d628ba0941eb4fea0666ac391d149a.png\" class=\"latex\" alt=\"$Q$\" style=\"vertical-align: -3px\" width=\"13\" height=\"16\" /> and <img src=\"//latex.artofproblemsolving.com/e/f/f/eff43e84f8a3bcf7b6965f0a3248bc4d3a9d0cd4.png\" class=\"latex\" alt=\"$R$\" width=\"14\" height=\"12\" />. Let <img src=\"//latex.artofproblemsolving.com/a/d/2/ad28c83c99a8fd0dd2e2e594c9d02ee532765a0a.png\" class=\"latex\" alt=\"$S$\" style=\"vertical-align: -1px\" width=\"14\" height=\"14\" /> be a point on <img src=\"//latex.artofproblemsolving.com/6/6/9/66981fa3920210c6ad8dbe5e968783d5dd7520c3.png\" class=\"latex\" alt=\"$\\gamma$\" style=\"vertical-align: -3px\" width=\"10\" height=\"11\" /> such that <img src=\"//latex.artofproblemsolving.com/5/e/b/5eb45550e2441065daf4fcfd0a006bd0beb24bc5.png\" class=\"latex\" alt=\"$BS \\parallel QR$\" style=\"vertical-align: -5px\" width=\"74\" height=\"19\" />. Prove that <img src=\"//latex.artofproblemsolving.com/4/3/3/4333690d7c22bb813e240b055e3ab4e2c27aceb2.png\" class=\"latex\" alt=\"$SA$\" width=\"25\" height=\"13\" /> bisects <img src=\"//latex.artofproblemsolving.com/9/a/7/9a7c52aff9dd9987076c0ac4fecccf59b6ed8bdb.png\" class=\"latex\" alt=\"$QR$\" style=\"vertical-align: -3px\" width=\"28\" height=\"16\" />.\n</p>\n<h2><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"Solution\">Solution</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/wiki/index.php?title=2000_Pan_African_MO_Problems/Problem_5&amp;action=edit&amp;section=1\" title=\"Edit section: Solution\">edit</a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h2>\n<p>There is a projective transformation which maps <img src=\"//latex.artofproblemsolving.com/6/6/9/66981fa3920210c6ad8dbe5e968783d5dd7520c3.png\" class=\"latex\" alt=\"$\\gamma$\" style=\"vertical-align: -3px\" width=\"10\" height=\"11\" /> to a circle and that maps the midpoint of <img src=\"//latex.artofproblemsolving.com/9/a/7/9a7c52aff9dd9987076c0ac4fecccf59b6ed8bdb.png\" class=\"latex\" alt=\"$QR$\" style=\"vertical-align: -3px\" width=\"28\" height=\"16\" /> to its center (EXPAND); therefore, we may assume without loss of generality that the midpoint of <img src=\"//latex.artofproblemsolving.com/9/a/7/9a7c52aff9dd9987076c0ac4fecccf59b6ed8bdb.png\" class=\"latex\" alt=\"$QR$\" style=\"vertical-align: -3px\" width=\"28\" height=\"16\" /> is the center of <img src=\"//latex.artofproblemsolving.com/6/6/9/66981fa3920210c6ad8dbe5e968783d5dd7520c3.png\" class=\"latex\" alt=\"$\\gamma$\" style=\"vertical-align: -3px\" width=\"10\" height=\"11\" />. But then <img src=\"//latex.artofproblemsolving.com/f/f/5/ff5fb3d775862e2123b007eb4373ff6cc1a34d4e.png\" class=\"latex\" alt=\"$B$\" width=\"14\" height=\"12\" /> is the reflection of <img src=\"//latex.artofproblemsolving.com/0/1/9/019e9892786e493964e145e7c5cf7b700314e53b.png\" class=\"latex\" alt=\"$A$\" width=\"13\" height=\"13\" /> across <img src=\"//latex.artofproblemsolving.com/9/a/7/9a7c52aff9dd9987076c0ac4fecccf59b6ed8bdb.png\" class=\"latex\" alt=\"$QR$\" style=\"vertical-align: -3px\" width=\"28\" height=\"16\" />, so that <img src=\"//latex.artofproblemsolving.com/a/d/2/ad28c83c99a8fd0dd2e2e594c9d02ee532765a0a.png\" class=\"latex\" alt=\"$S$\" style=\"vertical-align: -1px\" width=\"14\" height=\"14\" /> is the antipode of <img src=\"//latex.artofproblemsolving.com/0/1/9/019e9892786e493964e145e7c5cf7b700314e53b.png\" class=\"latex\" alt=\"$A$\" width=\"13\" height=\"13\" /> on <img src=\"//latex.artofproblemsolving.com/6/6/9/66981fa3920210c6ad8dbe5e968783d5dd7520c3.png\" class=\"latex\" alt=\"$\\gamma$\" style=\"vertical-align: -3px\" width=\"10\" height=\"11\" />, and we are done.\n</p>\n<h2><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"See_also\">See also</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/wiki/index.php?title=2000_Pan_African_MO_Problems/Problem_5&amp;action=edit&amp;section=2\" title=\"Edit section: See also\">edit</a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h2>\n<table class=\"wikitable\" style=\"clear:both; margin:0.5em auto; font-size:95%; border:1px solid black;\">\n<tbody><tr>\n<td style=\"background:#ccf;text-align:center;\" colspan=\"3\"><b><a href=\"/wiki/index.php/2000_Pan_African_MO\" title=\"2000 Pan African MO\">2000 Pan African MO</a></b> (<b><a href=\"/wiki/index.php/2000_Pan_African_MO_Problems\" title=\"2000 Pan African MO Problems\">Problems</a></b>)\n</td></tr>\n<tr>\n<td width=\"33%\" align=\"center\">Preceded&#160;by<br /><b><a href=\"/wiki/index.php/2000_Pan_African_MO_Problems/Problem_4\" title=\"2000 Pan African MO Problems/Problem 4\">Problem 4</a></b>\n</td>\n<td width=\"34%\" style=\"text-align:center;\"><a href=\"/wiki/index.php/2000_Pan_African_MO_Problems/Problem_1\" title=\"2000 Pan African MO Problems/Problem 1\">1</a> <b>•</b> <a href=\"/wiki/index.php/2000_Pan_African_MO_Problems/Problem_2\" title=\"2000 Pan African MO Problems/Problem 2\">2</a> <b>•</b> <a href=\"/wiki/index.php?title=2000_Pan_African_MO_Problems/Problem_3&amp;action=edit&amp;redlink=1\" class=\"new\" title=\"2000 Pan African MO Problems/Problem 3 (page does not exist)\">3</a> <b>•</b> <a href=\"/wiki/index.php/2000_Pan_African_MO_Problems/Problem_4\" title=\"2000 Pan African MO Problems/Problem 4\">4</a> <b>•</b> <a class=\"mw-selflink selflink\">5</a> <b>•</b> <a href=\"/wiki/index.php/2000_Pan_African_MO_Problems/Problem_6\" title=\"2000 Pan African MO Problems/Problem 6\">6</a>\n</td>\n<td width=\"33%\" align=\"center\" rowspan=\"1\">Followed&#160;by<br /><b><a href=\"/wiki/index.php/2000_Pan_African_MO_Problems/Problem_6\" title=\"2000 Pan African MO Problems/Problem 6\">Problem 6</a></b>\n</td></tr>\n<tr>\n<td align=\"center\" colspan=\"3\"><b><a href=\"/wiki/index.php/Pan_African_MO_Problems_and_Solutions\" title=\"Pan African MO Problems and Solutions\"> All Pan African MO Problems and Solutions</a></b>\n</td></tr></tbody></table> <p><i>This article is a stub.  Help us out by <span class=\"plainlinks\"><a rel=\"nofo